  <thing id="dei5CDienw" name="Dienw’r Anffodion" description="In Welsh lore, the “Nameless One of Misfortune” wandered aimlessly for thirteen years until a sister goddess revived him with her mystic drink, whereupon he remembered that he was actually Manawyddan, the Welsh god of sea and storms." compset="Deity" uniqueness="unique">
